    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "EFFECTIVE JUNE 1, 1944\nUNITED\nAIR LINES\nUnited\nTHE MAIN LINE AIRWAY\nPrinted in U.S.A.",
      "VANCOUVER, B. C.\nSEATTLE\nMONTREAL\nISLES ATY\nMINNEAPOLIS. SI. PAUL\nSALT LAKE CITY\nSAN FRANCISCOL\n• OAKLAND\nWASHINGTON\nKANSAS CITY\nFT. WORTH _ DALLAS\nI MEN! OM\nHOUSTON\nSAN ANTONIO\nNEW ORLEANS\nUNITED AIR LINES\nOTHER AIR LINES\nTEMPORARILY SUSPENDED\n• BROWNSVILLE\n18 CUBA, CENTRAL AND SOUTH AMENCI\nTHE Mainliners SERVE\nWASHINGTON, D. C.\nCHICAGO • TOLEDO • WASHINGTON\nonly 3¾ hours via\nUnited's Main Line Airway\nSHORT... DIRECT. ONLY 628 MILES\n• TWO FAST, ONE-STOP FLIGHTS DAILY-EACH WAY\nEASTBOUND Lv. CHICAGO Arr. TOLEDO\nArr. WASHINGTON\n9:00 AM\n11:19 AM\n1:49 PM\n11:45 AM\n4:34 PM\nWESTBOUND Lv. WASHINGTON\nArr. TOLEDO\nArr. CHICAGO\n5:00 PM\n0:10 PM\n7:00 PM\n9:30 PM\n10:15 PM\nAt Chicago— Mainliners to and from \"Everywhere West\"\nALSO . Frequent, convenient service to and from Washington\nvia United-PCA through the Cleveland gateway.\nUnited Airlines\nThe Main Bine Airway"
    ],
